  "prompt": "Is internal hard drive a primary storage device or secondary storage device?",
  "response": "An internal hard drive is considered a secondary storage device. Primary storage typically refers to temporary storage solutions such as RAM (Random Access Memory), which is used for data that is actively being processed. Secondary storage, on the other hand, refers to long-term storage options like internal hard drives, solid-state drives (SSDs), and optical discs, which store data persistently even when the computer is turned off.",
